'''Bhavana Radhakrishnan''' (born 28 July 1961) is a Carnatic singer and [[playback singer]] in [[Malayalam cinema]].<ref>{{cite news | title = Glowing tributes paid to Pattanakkad Purushothaman | newspaper=The Hindu| url = https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-kerala/glowing-tributes-paid-to-pattanakkad-purushothaman/article18430354.ece |date= 20 March 2006| accessdate = 16 January 2019 }}</ref> She received the 1997  [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Singer]] for the song "Ennodenthini pinakkam" in the film ''[[Kaliyattam]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=STATE FILM AWARDS: 1997|publisher=Official website of [[Department of Information and Public Relations (Kerala)]], Govt. of Kerala|url=http://www.prd.kerala.gov.in/stateawards3.htm|page=3|accessdate=2014-05-04|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303234157/http://www.prd.kerala.gov.in/stateawards3.htm|archivedate=2016-03-03|df=}}</ref>

She was awarded a doctorate in music by the University Of Kerala.{{Citation needed|date= May 2018}} She is a music educator and currently working as associate professor  in [[Carnatic music]] at [[SN College, Kollam]]. She is also known as a performer of [[devotional music]].<ref>{{cite web| title = Spiritual songs for the soul|publisher= The Hindu| url = http://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/music/spiritual-songs-for-the-soul/article5557407.ece# |date=9 January 2014| accessdate = 2014-05-04 | first = Nita | last = Sathyendran }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title = Avar Kandumuttumbol: Systematic music life|publisher = [[Mathrubhumi News]]|url = http://mathrubhuminews.in/ee/Programs/Episode/4446/systematic-music-life-avar-kandumuttumbol-episode-49/E|date = |accessdate = 2014-05-05}}</ref>

